    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-07-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="481"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <head>No. 481.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Manning</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-07-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 14, 1887</date>. (Received July
                        22.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 179.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave to call your attention to my No. 76,
                    of February 28 last, inclosing Mr. Mariscal’s note to me of the 25th, offering
                    to return certain property which had been delivered to the authorities of the
                    State of Chihuahua by United States Army officers, and also to pay $500, the
                    estimated value of other property also delivered to the same authorities, and
                    which had been lost. In his note Mr. Mariscal requests that some person be
                    appointed by the United States Government to receive the property and the
                    money.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Th. C. Manning.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
